                            <comment id="17173403" author="dongjoon" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2020 18:31:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rsivaram&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rsivaram&quot;&gt;rsivaram&lt;/a&gt;. Is this only 2.6.0 issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17174223" author="rsivaram" created="Mon, 10 Aug 2020 10:17:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dongjoon&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dongjoon&quot;&gt;dongjoon&lt;/a&gt; This is not a 2.6.0 issue, ReplicaNotAvailable has always been non-retriable. This turned out to be a bigger issue in non-Java consumers since fetch-from-follower was introduced in&#160; 2.4.0. Java consumers always handled this case correctly and were not affected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17175094" author="dongjoon" created="Mon, 10 Aug 2020 23:05:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the confirmation, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rsivaram&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rsivaram&quot;&gt;rsivaram&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
